Learn About the Template Bot: Check Order Status

The Check Order Status dialog skill allows users to check on their order. It starts with the Check the status of an order dialog, which asks if the end user has their order number and guides the conversation based on the response.

If they have their order number, the bot asks for it and moves to the Order look up dialog, which launches a flow to search for the order using the order number. If not, the bot transfers to an agent.

The rest of this dialog guides the conversation based on whether the order status variable is filled. If filled, the bot moves to the Order Found dialog, where the order number, amount, and status are reported to the user. The bot then asks if they want to update, cancel, or return an order.

If the variable isnâ€™t filled, the bot moves to the Order Not Found dialog, notifies the customer that the order wasn't found, and transfers to the Anything Else? dialog.

Available in Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
